cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper is about a deep learning approach for removing rain streaks from single images, which is a common problem in computer vision and image processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a new semi-supervised GAN-based deraining network, which involves both supervised and unsupervised processes, and uses both synthetic and real rainy images. This suggests that the paper may also belong to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.GR (Graphics), which are related to deep learning, generative models, and image synthesis. Finally, the paper also introduces a new real-world rainy image dataset, which could be relevant to the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia).
